          "vnum": 2568,
          "name": "Underground Crevasse",
          "description": "A long, narrow crevasse splits the bottom of a broad cavern underneath the shores of Mareldja. Sand filters in through an opening here with steps leading upward. The crevasse is filled with seawater which ebbs and flows with the tidal currents. A series of wooden planks form a rickety bridge spanning the crevasse, to the north.",
