        "2571": {
          "vnum": 2571,
          "name": "Crevasse Ledge",
          "description": "You are upon a thin ledge next to a tunnel entrance several meters below the surface. A rickety wooden bridge spans a water-filled crevasse to the south, its waters casting a chilly, dull blow glow. Deposits of loose sand and encrusted salt cover the surfaces. The tunnel leads northeast.",
