          "vnum": 1004,
          "name": "Top of the Slope",
          "description": "You have come to the summit of a steep slope which drops down to the south. The briny smell of the sea rises from the west where you can see the vast curve of the horizon in the distance. The outskirts of a forest can be seen to the northeast. The roar of a crowd can be heard from the canvas tents set to your east.",
